{
  "document_id": "col-43",
  "title": "Colossians 43",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "The pride of the higher realms is the clear vault of the sky,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "The sun, when it appears, proclaims as it rises"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "At noon it parches the land,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "A man tending a furnace works in burning heat,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Great is the Lord who made it;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "It is the moon that marks the changing seasons,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "From the moon comes the sign for festal days,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "The new moon, as its name suggests, renews itself;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "The glory of the stars is the beauty of heaven,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "On the orders of the Holy One they stand in their appointed places;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Look at the rainbow and praise him who made it;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "It encircles the sky with its glorious arc;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "By his command he sends the driving snow"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "Therefore the storehouses are opened,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "In his majesty he gives the clouds their strength,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "when he appears, the mountains shake."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "The voice of his thunder causes the earth to tremble;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "The eye is dazzled by the beauty of its whiteness,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "He pours frost over the earth like salt,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "The cold north wind blows,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "He consumes the mountains and burns up the wilderness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "A mist quickly heals all things;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "By his plan he stilled the deep"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "Those who sail the sea tell of its dangers,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "In it are strange and marvelous creatures,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "Because of him each of his messengers succeeds,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "We could say more but could never say enough;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "Where can we find the strength to praise him?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Awesome is the Lord and very great,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "Glorify the Lord and exalt him as much as you can,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "Who has seen him and can describe him?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "Many things greater than these lie hidden,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "col-43-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "For the Lord has made all things,"
    }
  ]
}